refreshes the repository-backed home state on each route render so the feed sections reflect current liked/search/filter state whenever the route is entered or updated.\",\n93:         \"`FoodikeBootstrap` stores home query/filter route state and `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` rebuilds ads, categories, favourites, and restaurants from current repositories on each render.\",\n94:         \"`HomeStore` mirrors the state aggregation without any permission flow.\",\n95:         \"`buildHomeRoute` recomputes `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` from repository data when the home route renders, preserving entry-time feed loading.\",\n96:         \"`HomeStore.loadAdvertisements()`, `loadRecommendedCategories()`, `loadFavouriteRestaurants()`, and `loadRestaurantCatalog()` now name the translated repository-backed state slices explicitly, while `buildVisibleState(...)` and `buildFilteredState(...)` pres...\",\n97:         \"`renderSearchBar` and `usesLocalSearchState()` keep only route-local query state without any preference persistence.\",\n98:         \"`renderSearchBar` feeds route-level query state into `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` and `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)`, enabling immediate home/history filtering from the shared search surface.\",\n99:         \"`buildHistoryRoute` reloads `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)` on each route render so the current liked-restaurant state is reflected whenever the page is entered or updated.\",\n100:         \"`HistoryStore` plus `FoodikeBootstrap` route state expose observable search/tab state and reload the repository-backed favourites list on each rebuild.\",\n101:         \"`bootstrap_page.cj` keeps `homeSelectedFilter` in route state, and `buildFilterRow` re-renders selected styling while `HomeStore.buildFilteredState(...)` applies the active chip to visible lists.\",\n102:         \"`FoodikeBootstrap::buildHistoryRoute` binds current query/tab state and recomputes `HistoryStore.buildVisibleState(...)` whenever the history route is shown.\",\n103:         \"`HomeStore::toggleFilter(...)` and `matchesTag(...)` preserve the source chip-selection semantics by resolving the tapped filter string into the corresponding visible-list predicate.\",\n104:         \"`HomePageState` remains a pure translated state container with no permission path.\",\n105:         \"`HistoryPageState` and the route-local history state fields keep equivalent plain state for favourites, records, query, and tab selection without any permission handling.\"\n106:       ],\n107:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n108:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n109:       ],\n110:       \"riskHints\": [\n111:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n112:       ],\n113:       \"matrixRows\": [\n114:         {\n115:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n116:           \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-home-ef0657c4ea-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n117:           \"featureName\": \"Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refresh, or teardown behavior.\",\n118:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/home/HomeScreen.kt\",\n119:           \"importance\": \"critical\",\n120:           \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-04-home-history\",\n121:           \"status\": \"implemented\",\n122:           \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n123:           \"verdict\": \"complete\",\n124:           \"reasons\": [\n125:             \"implemented with behavior, parity, endpoint, and verification evidence\"\n126:           ],\n127:           \"targetEndpoints\": [\n128:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::buildHomeRoute\",\n129:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/home/home_store.cj::buildFilteredState\"\n130:           ],\n131:      